  "texts": [
    "In contrast, this thesis aims to develop a method for general real-time systems where simulators for specific real-time operating systems may not be available.",
    "Our approach does not rely on simulators, making it more broadly applicable to a variety of real-time systems.Chapter 4 ApproachIn this chapter, we delve into the methodologies employed to estimate the WCET of the selected real-time robotic algorithms.",
    "First, we introduce the case studies and algorithms serving as subjects of this thesis, providing a context for explaining and validating our methods.",
    "Next, we describe how GAs and RL can be used to measure WCET for each subject.",
    "Case StudiesReal-time robotic algorithms, such as collision detection, are crucial components of many modern real-time applications."
  ]
}